result.name: KamuKura Japanese Restaurant

reviews.text: Ate lunch here, Fine Japanese restaurant but nothing special , a bit overpriced,

The sushi here is delicious and freshly made. I highly recommend the tofu skin rolls and avocado handrolls (vegan if you ask for no mayonnaise). Also the service here is so great - I made a reservation once, and now they remember my name 😊

It's small but very busy, so there may be delays at peak times. Good idea to make reservations (unless you're dining alone and happy to sit at the counter), especially on the weekend.
As a Japanese restaurant in Kennedy town, it's a time honoured restaurant in the district.
Good service and reasonably priced.
It's not exactly traditional japanese food but for convenience and time saving sake, it'll do.
